ZCZC GE11
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
SUNDAY EVENING THE UK LIES BETWEEN AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 997 LOCATED
BETWEEN ICELAND AND NORWAY IN THE ARCTIC OCEAN AND HIGH PRESSURE 1032 FM
THE AZORES CENTRED TO THE SW OF THE UK. THE HIGH WILL STEADILY RETREAT BACK
TOWARDS THE AZORES AS ANOTHER LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM SPAWNS TO THE W OF PORTPATRICK
EARLY ON MONDAY. THIS LOW WILL MOV ACROSS SCOTLAND DURING MONDAY BEFORE DECAYING
AS A RENEWED RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE THEN BUILDS ACROSS THE UK AND CULLERCOATS
ON TUESDAY. HOWEVER BY THE END OF THIS PERIOD A SHALLOW LOW PRESSURE WILL
BE CENTRED OVER SERN SCANDINAVIA AND A BROADER AND DEEPER LOW WILL BE APPROACHING
SW ICELAND LEAVING CULLERCOATS IN BETWEEN WEATHER SYSTEMS ON WEDNESDAY.
STRG TO GALE FORCE WINDS MAY AFFECT CENTRAL PARTS OF CULLERCOATS DURING SUNDAY
EVENING AND MONDAY SPREADING TO SERN PARTS OF THE AREA BEFORE CLEARING
BY EARLY TUESDAY. OTHERWISE WINDS WILL BE NON-HAZARDOUS
